						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the image of Perumāl in the threshing ground, back side.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1566, Svabhānu, Pushya ba. 30</hi> and it corresponds to 1643 A.D., December, 30th Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and worn out. Seems to record a gift of village for the worship of god Kēśava Perumāḷ. Other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
